Cu(In, Ga)Se2, a highly compensated semiconductor, has many more donors and acceptors (~1019) than free charge carriers (holes ~1017)45. At high enough temperatures where the donors and acceptors are ionized, the net free carrier concentration is the difference between the number of donors and acceptors shown in equation (6), where ND is donor concentration, NA is acceptor concentration and Nt is total free carrier concentration.6Nt=ND+NA,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
